VALUES
(43, 10, 9, 19, 95, 7, 7, 'pasture', 'Connection of Pasture and Sheep', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''pasture'' and the relationship between God and His people as ''sheep.'' This connection highlights the idea of divine care and guidance for those who enter through the ''door'' of salvation.', 'theme', 0.503, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 9, 19, 100, 3, 4, 'find pasture', 'Connection of Pasture and Entry', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of entering into a place of safety and provision. John 10:9 speaks of entering through the door to find pasture, while Psalms 100:3-4 invites entering into God''s gates and courts, highlighting a communal relationship with God as shepherd.', 'theme', 0.503, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 9, 23, 40, 11, 11, 'find pasture', 'Shepherd and Door Imagery', 'This connection highlights the themes of guidance and provision found in both passages. John 10:9 speaks of salvation and finding pasture, while Isaiah 40:11 describes the shepherd feeding and leading his flock.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 10, 42, 19, 10, 10, 'that they might have life', 'Connection of Purpose in Mission', 'Both passages emphasize the purpose of Jesus'' mission. John 10:10 speaks of bringing life abundantly, while Luke 19:10 highlights seeking and saving the lost, indicating a focus on restoration and abundance.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 10, 43, 3, 17, 17, 'that they might have life', 'Connection of Purpose in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the purpose of Jesus'' coming. John 10:10 highlights the abundant life He offers, while John 3:17 underscores His mission to save rather than condemn.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 10, 43, 6, 33, 33, 'life', 'Life and Abundance Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of life. John 10:10 speaks of abundant life, while John 6:33 refers to giving life to the world.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 10, 40, 20, 28, 28, 'that they might have life', 'Life and Ransom Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the purpose of Jesus'' coming. John 10:10 speaks of giving life abundantly, while Matthew 20:28 highlights giving his life as a ransom, indicating a sacrificial aspect that leads to life.', 'theme', 0.8459999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 10, 54, 1, 15, 15, 'I am come that they might have life', 'Life and Salvation Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the purpose of Christ''s coming: to bring life and salvation. John 10:10 speaks of abundant life, while 1 Timothy 1:15 highlights saving sinners, linking the concepts of life and redemption.', 'theme', 0.8459999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 10, 58, 7, 25, 25, 'life', 'Life and Salvation Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of life and salvation. John 10:10 speaks of abundant life, while Hebrews 7:25 emphasizes the ability to save completely.', 'theme', 0.804, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 10, 26, 34, 2, 4, NULL, 'Shepherds and Abundant Life', 'Both passages emphasize the role of leaders in providing for their followers. In John 10:10, Jesus contrasts His mission of giving life with the destructive actions of thieves, while Ezekiel 34:2-4 condemns the shepherds for failing to care for their flock, highlighting the importance of nurturing and protecting those in their charge.', 'theme', 0.7409999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 11, 43, 10, 14, 15, NULL, 'Connection of the Good Shepherd', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the good shepherd who lays down his life for the sheep. This connection highlights the intimate relationship between the shepherd and the sheep, as well as the sacrificial nature of the shepherd''s love.', 'theme', 0.671, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 11, 19, 23, 1, 1, 'shepherd', 'Shepherd Imagery in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the shepherd, highlighting care and sacrifice. John 10:11 presents the shepherd giving his life, while Psalms 23:1 assures that the shepherd provides for the sheep.', 'theme', 0.657, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 11, 43, 15, 13, 13, NULL, 'Sacrificial Love in John', 'This connection highlights the theme of sacrificial love, as both passages emphasize the act of laying down one''s life. In John 10:11, the good shepherd gives his life for the sheep, while John 15:13 states that the greatest love is to lay down one''s life for friends.', 'theme', 0.643, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 11, 66, 7, 17, 17, 'the good shepherd giveth his life', 'Shepherd and Lamb Imagery', 'This connection highlights the role of the shepherd and the Lamb in providing care and guidance to the faithful. Both passages emphasize the sacrificial nature of the shepherd and the nurturing aspect of the Lamb, who leads to sustenance and comfort.', 'theme', 0.601, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 11, 23, 40, 11, 11, 'shepherd', 'Shepherd Imagery in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the shepherd in caring for the flock. John 10:11 highlights the good shepherd''s sacrifice, while Isaiah 40:11 describes the shepherd''s nurturing actions.', 'theme', 0.573, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 11, 60, 2, 24, 25, 'the good shepherd giveth his life', 'Shepherd and Sacrifice Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the shepherd who sacrifices for the sheep. John 10:11 presents Jesus as the good shepherd, while 1 Peter 2:25 refers to believers as sheep returning to their shepherd after being lost.', 'theme', 0.5589999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 11, 62, 3, 16, 16, 'giveth his life for the sheep', 'Love and Sacrifice Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of laying down one''s life for others. John 10:11 speaks of the good shepherd giving his life for the sheep, while 1 John 3:16 highlights that we ought to lay down our lives for the brethren, reflecting the same sacrificial love.', 'theme', 0.489, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 12, 44, 20, 29, 29, 'the wolf', 'Wolves and the Flock', 'Both passages emphasize the danger posed by wolves to the flock. John 10:12 describes the hireling fleeing from the wolf, while Acts 20:29 warns of grievous wolves entering among the believers.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 12, 61, 2, 3, 3, 'leaveth the sheep', 'Connection of False Shepherds', 'Both passages emphasize the danger of those who exploit others for personal gain. In John 10:12, the hireling abandons the sheep, while 2 Peter 2:3 warns of those who make merchandise of believers. This connection highlights the theme of false leaders who prioritize their own interests over the well-being of the flock.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 12, 26, 34, 2, 6, 'leaveth the sheep', 'Shepherds and Their Flocks', 'Both passages emphasize the failure of shepherds to protect and care for their sheep. John highlights the hireling''s abandonment of the flock in danger, while Ezekiel condemns shepherds for neglecting and exploiting the sheep.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 12, 38, 11, 16, 17, 'leaveth the sheep', 'Shepherd and Hireling Contrast', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the shepherd and the consequences of neglecting the flock. John highlights the hireling''s abandonment of the sheep in danger, while Zechariah warns against the idol shepherd who fails to care for the flock.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 12, 40, 10, 16, 16, NULL, 'Sheep and Wolves Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the vulnerability of sheep in the presence of wolves. John highlights the danger posed by wolves to the sheep, while Matthew directly states that the disciples are sent as sheep among wolves.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 12, 23, 56, 10, 12, 'the shepherd', 'Shepherds and Hirelings', 'Both passages emphasize the failure of shepherds to protect their sheep. John speaks of hirelings fleeing from danger, while Isaiah describes blind watchmen and greedy shepherds who neglect their duties.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 12, 40, 7, 15, 15, 'wolf', 'Connection of Shepherd and Wolves', 'Both passages emphasize the danger posed by wolves to the sheep. John 10:12 describes the hireling fleeing from the wolf, while Matthew 7:15 warns of false prophets as ravening wolves in disguise.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 13, 43, 12, 6, 6, 'careth not for the sheep', 'Care for the Sheep', 'This connection highlights the lack of genuine care in both passages. The hireling''s indifference to the sheep parallels Judas''s selfishness, as he does not care for the poor but for his own gain.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 13, 50, 2, 20, 20, 'careth not for the sheep', 'Care for the Sheep', 'This connection highlights the theme of care and responsibility. In John 10:13, the hireling does not care for the sheep, while Philippians 2:20 emphasizes the importance of caring for others'' state.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 13, 44, 18, 17, 17, 'careth not for the sheep', 'Carelessness of Leaders', 'This connection highlights the theme of leaders who do not care for those they are responsible for. In both passages, the hireling and Gallio exhibit a lack of concern for the well-being of others, emphasizing their indifference.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 14, 43, 10, 27, 27, NULL, 'Shepherd and Sheep Relationship', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the shepherd and the sheep. The phrases ''know my sheep'' and ''I know them'' highlight the mutual recognition and connection between them.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 14, 55, 2, 19, 19, 'know my sheep', 'Shepherd and Knowing His Own', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of God knowing His people. In John 10:14, the good shepherd knows his sheep, while 2 Timothy 2:19 states, ''The Lord knoweth them that are his.'' This connection highlights the intimate relationship between God and His followers.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 14, 43, 10, 11, 11, 'I am the good shepherd', 'Connection of Good Shepherd Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the good shepherd. In John 10:14, the shepherd knows his sheep, while in John 10:11, he sacrifices his life for them.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
