(43, 10, 14, 49, 1, 17, 17, 'know my sheep', 'Knowledge of the Shepherd', 'This connection highlights the theme of knowledge in both passages. In John 10:14, the relationship between the shepherd and the sheep emphasizes being known, while Ephesians 1:17 speaks of gaining knowledge of God through wisdom and revelation.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 14, 62, 5, 20, 20, 'know my sheep', 'Shepherd and Knowledge Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of knowing and being known. In John 10:14, the good shepherd knows his sheep, while 1 John 5:20 emphasizes knowing him that is true. Both passages stress the importance of relationship and understanding.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 14, 19, 1, 6, 6, 'know my sheep', 'Shepherd and Righteous Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine knowledge and care. Both passages emphasize that the Lord knows those who are righteous, akin to the good shepherd knowing his sheep.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 14, 55, 1, 12, 12, 'know my sheep', 'Shepherd and Belief Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between knowing and being known. In John 10:14, the good shepherd knows his sheep, while in 2 Timothy 1:12, the speaker expresses confidence in knowing whom he has believed.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 15, 43, 10, 11, 11, 'lay down my life for the sheep', 'Shepherd and Sacrifice Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the shepherd who lays down his life for the sheep. This connection highlights the sacrificial nature of the good shepherd, linking the identity of Jesus with his mission of sacrifice.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 15, 48, 1, 4, 4, 'I lay down my life for the sheep', 'Connection of Sacrificial Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the act of Jesus giving himself for others. In John 10:15, he lays down his life for the sheep, while Galatians 1:4 speaks of him giving himself for our sins.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 15, 23, 53, 10, 10, 'lay down my life for the sheep', 'Sacrificial Themes in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of sacrifice. John 10:15 speaks of laying down life for the sheep, while Isaiah 53:10 mentions making his soul an offering for sin.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 15, 60, 3, 18, 18, 'lay down my life for the sheep', 'Connection of Christ''s Sacrifice', 'Both passages emphasize Christ''s sacrificial role. John 10:15 highlights laying down His life for the sheep, while 1 Peter 3:18 speaks of suffering for sins, linking the themes of sacrifice and redemption.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 15, 62, 2, 2, 2, 'lay down my life for the sheep', 'Connection of Sacrifice and Atonement', 'This connection highlights the theme of Jesus'' sacrificial role. Both passages emphasize His laying down of life and being a propitiation for sins.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 15, 40, 11, 27, 27, 'even so know I the Father', 'Knowledge of the Father and Son', 'Both passages emphasize the intimate knowledge between the Father and the Son. John 10:15 states, ''I know the Father,'' while Matthew 11:27 highlights that ''no man knoweth the Son, but the Father.''', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 15, 38, 13, 7, 7, 'lay down my life for the sheep', 'Connection of Shepherd and Sacrifice', 'This connection highlights the theme of the shepherd''s sacrifice. In John 10:15, Jesus lays down his life for the sheep, while Zechariah 13:7 speaks of a shepherd being smitten, leading to the scattering of the sheep.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 16, 23, 56, 8, 8, 'other sheep I have', 'Gathering of the Outcasts', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering of those outside the current fold. John speaks of ''other sheep'' while Isaiah mentions ''others to him,'' highlighting a theme of inclusion.', 'theme', 0.524, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 16, 43, 11, 52, 52, 'one fold, and one shepherd', 'Gathering of God''s Children', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering of God''s people into one fold. John 10:16 speaks of bringing together sheep from different folds, while John 11:52 mentions gathering the scattered children of God.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 16, 60, 2, 25, 25, 'one fold, and one shepherd', 'Shepherd and Sheep Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of sheep and a shepherd. John 10:16 mentions ''one fold, and one shepherd,'' while 1 Peter 2:25 refers to ''the Shepherd and Bishop of your souls.'' This connection highlights the unity and guidance provided by the shepherd.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 16, 26, 34, 23, 23, 'one fold, and one shepherd', 'Shepherd and One Fold Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of one shepherd uniting the flock. John 10:16 refers to ''one fold,'' while Ezekiel 34:23 mentions ''one shepherd'' over the people.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 16, 49, 2, 13, 18, 'one fold, and one shepherd', 'Unity of Believers in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of unity among believers, highlighting that Jesus brings together those who are ''far off'' and ''not of this fold'' into one body. This connection illustrates the breaking down of barriers and the creation of one community under Christ.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 16, 26, 37, 24, 24, 'one shepherd', 'One Shepherd Theme Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''one shepherd'' uniting the people. John 10:16 refers to bringing other sheep into one fold, while Ezekiel 37:24 speaks of David as king over them with one shepherd.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 16, 43, 6, 37, 37, 'one fold, and one shepherd', 'Unity of Believers and Acceptance', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering of believers under one shepherd. John 10:16 speaks of bringing together ''other sheep,'' while John 6:37 assures that all given by the Father will come without rejection.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 17, 43, 10, 18, 18, 'lay down my life', 'Connection of Life and Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of Jesus'' authority over his life and death. The phrase ''lay down my life'' in the source verse directly links to the assertion of power in the target passage.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 17, 43, 10, 11, 11, 'lay down my life', 'Shepherd and Sacrifice Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of sacrifice, with Jesus as the good shepherd who lays down his life. The act of laying down his life connects directly to the Father''s love for him.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 17, 58, 2, 9, 9, 'lay down my life', 'Connection of Sacrificial Death', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of Jesus laying down his life for others. John 10:17 highlights His voluntary sacrifice, while Hebrews 2:9 speaks to His suffering of death for every man.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 17, 23, 53, 7, 12, 'lay down my life', 'Sacrificial Themes in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of laying down one''s life as a sacrificial act. John 10:17 speaks of laying down life to take it again, while Isaiah 53:7-12 describes the suffering servant who bears the iniquities of many, highlighting the theme of sacrificial love and redemption.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 17, 23, 42, 1, 1, 'my Father love me, because I lay down my life', 'Servanthood and Sacrifice Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of sacrificial service. Both passages emphasize the idea of a chosen servant who lays down his life for others, reflecting God''s delight in His servant''s mission.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 18, 56, 2, 14, 14, 'I lay it down of myself', 'Self-Sacrifice for Redemption', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of self-sacrifice. John 10:18 speaks of Jesus laying down his life, while Titus 2:14 highlights that he gave himself for us to redeem us from iniquity.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 18, 58, 2, 9, 9, 'I lay it down of myself', 'Connection of Jesus'' Death', 'This connection highlights Jesus'' voluntary sacrifice and the significance of His death. Both passages emphasize His authority over death and His role in suffering for humanity.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 18, 43, 2, 19, 21, 'I have power to lay it down', 'Jesus'' Authority Over His Body', 'This connection highlights Jesus'' authority over his own life and body. In both passages, he speaks of laying down his life and raising it again, emphasizing his power and control over death.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 18, 43, 10, 17, 17, NULL, 'Connection of Life and Death', 'Both passages emphasize the act of laying down life and the authority to take it again. This connection highlights the relationship between Jesus'' voluntary sacrifice and the love of the Father.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 18, 23, 53, 10, 12, 'I lay it down of myself', 'Sacrificial Offering Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of voluntary sacrifice. In John 10:18, Jesus emphasizes his power to lay down his life, paralleling Isaiah 53:10, which speaks of making his soul an offering for sin.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 18, 58, 5, 6, 9, 'I have power to lay it down', 'Connection of Obedience and Sacrifice', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of voluntary sacrifice. In John 10:18, Jesus asserts his power to lay down his life, while Hebrews 5:8 highlights his obedience through suffering. This connection highlights the significance of Jesus'' actions in relation to salvation.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 18, 50, 2, 6, 8, 'lay it down of myself', 'Connection of Obedience and Sacrifice', 'This connection highlights the theme of voluntary sacrifice and obedience. Both passages emphasize the act of laying down one''s life and becoming obedient unto death.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
