VALUES
(43, 10, 25, 43, 10, 38, 38, 'the works that I do in my Fathers name', 'Connection of Works and Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of Jesus'' works as evidence of his divine authority. In each verse, Jesus invites belief based on the works he performs in his Father''s name.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 25, 43, 8, 58, 58, 'the works that I do', 'Witness to Jesus'' Identity', 'This connection highlights Jesus'' assertion of His divine identity. In both passages, He emphasizes His pre-existence and authority, with His works bearing witness to who He is.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 25, 44, 10, 38, 38, 'the works that I do in my Fathers name', 'Connection of Jesus'' Works', 'Both passages emphasize the works of Jesus as evidence of his divine authority. In John, Jesus states that his works bear witness of him, while Acts describes how he went about doing good and healing, showcasing God''s presence with him.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 25, 58, 2, 3, 3, 'the works that I do in my Fathers name', 'Witness of Salvation', 'This connection highlights the theme of witness and confirmation of Jesus'' works and teachings. Both passages emphasize the importance of believing in the message and the evidence provided by Jesus'' actions and those who heard him.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 25, 44, 2, 22, 22, 'the works that I do in my Fathers name', 'Connection of Miracles and Witness', 'Both passages emphasize the role of miracles as evidence of Jesus'' divine approval. In John, Jesus refers to his works as a witness, while Acts highlights the miracles performed by Jesus as proof of his divine endorsement.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 26, 43, 8, 47, 47, NULL, 'Connection of Belief and Hearing', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between belonging to God and the ability to hear His words. In John 10:26, the lack of belief is linked to not being among Jesus'' sheep, while John 8:47 states that those who are of God hear His words. This connection highlights the theme of spiritual discernment based on one''s relationship with God.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 26, 47, 4, 3, 4, NULL, 'Connection of Belief and Blindness', 'This connection highlights the theme of belief and its absence. Both passages emphasize that those who do not believe are separated from the truth, with John noting they are ''not of my sheep'' and 2 Corinthians stating they are ''lost'' and blinded.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 26, 43, 6, 65, 65, 'ye believe not', 'Connection of Divine Selection', 'Both passages emphasize the idea that belief and coming to Jesus are contingent upon divine selection. In John 10:26, the lack of belief is linked to not being part of His sheep, while John 6:65 states that coming to Jesus is given by the Father.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 26, 45, 11, 7, 8, 'ye believe not, because ye are not of my sheep', 'Connection of Belief and Blinding', 'This connection highlights the theme of belief and spiritual blindness. In John 10:26, the lack of belief is linked to not being part of Jesus'' sheep, while Romans 11:7-8 discusses Israel''s failure to obtain understanding due to being blinded.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 26, 62, 4, 6, 6, 'ye believe not', 'Belief and Knowledge of God', 'This connection highlights the relationship between belief and belonging to God. Both passages emphasize that those who do not belong to God do not recognize His voice or truth.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 27, 43, 10, 16, 16, 'hear my voice', 'Connection of the Sheep Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of sheep hearing the shepherd''s voice. In John 10:27, the sheep recognize and follow the shepherd, while John 10:16 introduces other sheep who will also hear his voice, indicating a unified flock under one shepherd.', 'theme', 0.7899999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 27, 66, 3, 20, 20, 'hear my voice', 'Connection of Hearing His Voice', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of hearing Jesus'' voice. In John 10:27, the sheep recognize and follow Him, while Revelation 3:20 invites individuals to hear His voice and respond. This connection highlights the call to relationship and communion with Christ.', 'theme', 0.643, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 27, 46, 8, 3, 3, 'I know them', 'Knowing God and His Followers', 'This connection highlights the theme of being known by God. In both passages, the idea of being recognized by God is emphasized, as His followers are known by Him and those who love God are also known by Him.', 'theme', 0.629, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 27, 43, 10, 3, 4, NULL, 'Connection of Sheep and Voice', 'Both passages emphasize that the sheep hear the shepherd''s voice and follow him. This connection highlights the relationship between the shepherd and his sheep, illustrating recognition and guidance.', 'theme', 0.601, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 27, 58, 3, 7, 7, 'hear my voice', 'Hearing His Voice', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of hearing God''s voice. In John 10:27, the sheep recognize and follow the voice of the shepherd, while Hebrews 3:7 urges listeners to hear His voice today.', 'theme', 0.5589999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 27, 48, 4, 9, 9, 'I know them', 'Connection of Knowing God', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship of knowing and being known. In John, the sheep hear the voice of the shepherd, while in Galatians, being known of God is highlighted, suggesting a mutual recognition.', 'theme', 0.496, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 27, 11, 18, 21, 21, 'follow me', 'Following the Voice of God', 'This connection highlights the theme of following God. In John 10:27, the sheep hear and follow the voice of Jesus, while in 1 Kings 18:21, Elijah challenges the people to choose whom to follow, emphasizing the need for decisive allegiance.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 28, 43, 6, 39, 40, 'eternal life', 'Eternal Life Assurance', 'Both passages emphasize the promise of eternal life for believers. John 10:28 assures that they shall never perish, while John 6:39-40 highlights that none will be lost and will be raised on the last day.', 'theme', 0.9019999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 28, 43, 3, 15, 16, 'shall never perish', 'Eternal Life and Perishing', 'Both passages emphasize the promise of eternal life and the assurance that believers shall not perish. This connection highlights the security of salvation offered through faith in Jesus.', 'theme', 0.671, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 28, 58, 7, 25, 25, 'eternal life', 'Eternal Security of Believers', 'Both passages emphasize the assurance of salvation. John 10:28 speaks of eternal life and security, while Hebrews 7:25 highlights the ability to save completely and intercede for believers.', 'theme', 0.657, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 28, 45, 8, 29, 29, 'eternal life', 'Eternal Life and Predestination', 'This connection highlights the assurance of eternal life in John 10:28 and the predestination to be conformed to Christ''s image in Romans 8:29. Both passages emphasize God''s sovereignty in granting believers security and purpose.', 'theme', 0.601, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 28, 50, 1, 6, 6, 'eternal life', 'Eternal Security in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the assurance of salvation. John 10:28 speaks of eternal life and security in Christ''s hand, while Philippians 1:6 assures that God will continue His work in believers until the end.', 'theme', 0.58, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 28, 23, 54, 17, 17, 'shall never perish', 'Eternal Protection and Security', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine protection in both passages. John 10:28 assures believers of eternal life and security, while Isaiah 54:17 emphasizes that no weapon formed against God''s servants shall prosper.', 'theme', 0.573, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 28, 62, 2, 25, 25, 'eternal life', 'Eternal Life Promise Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of eternal life. John 10:28 assures believers of eternal life, while 1 John 2:25 explicitly states it as a promise.', 'theme', 0.524, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 29, 43, 6, 37, 37, NULL, 'Divine Assurance of Believers', 'Both passages emphasize the security of those given to Jesus by the Father. John 10:29 highlights that no one can take them from the Father''s hand, while John 6:37 assures that all given will come and not be cast out.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 29, 43, 17, 2, 2, 'my Fathers hand', 'Divine Authority and Protection', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine authority, as both passages emphasize the power of the Father in relation to those given to the Son. In John 10:29, the Fathers hand protects believers, while John 17:2 speaks of the Son''s authority to grant eternal life to those given by the Father.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 29, 39, 1, 14, 14, 'greater than all', 'Divine Authority and Protection', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s supremacy and the protection He offers. Both passages emphasize the greatness of God, with John 10:29 stating that the Father is greater than all, while Malachi 1:14 refers to God as a great King.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 29, 2, 18, 11, 11, 'greater than all', 'God''s Supremacy Over All', 'Both passages emphasize the greatness of God, with John 10:29 highlighting the Father''s power to protect believers, while Exodus 18:11 declares the Lord''s superiority over all gods. This connection highlights the theme of divine authority and protection.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 29, 19, 145, 3, 3, 'greater than all', 'God''s Greatness and Protection', 'Both passages emphasize the greatness of God. John 10:29 highlights God''s protective power, while Psalms 145:3 declares His greatness as unsearchable.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 29, 27, 4, 3, 3, 'greater than all', 'Divine Sovereignty and Protection', 'Both passages emphasize the greatness of Gods power and authority. John 10:29 speaks of the Fathers protective hand, while Daniel 4:3 highlights His everlasting dominion and might.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
