VALUES
(43, 10, 39, 43, 7, 30, 30, NULL, 'Attempts to Seize Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the attempts to take Jesus, highlighting the tension surrounding his ministry. In each instance, the efforts to seize him are thwarted, indicating a divine timing at play.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 39, 43, 8, 59, 59, 'escaped out of their hand', 'Escape from Danger', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' ability to evade harm. In John 10:39, he escapes from those seeking to seize him, while in John 8:59, he hides from those ready to stone him.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 39, 43, 7, 44, 44, NULL, 'Attempts to Seize Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the attempts to take Jesus, highlighting the tension surrounding his ministry. In John 7:44, some would have taken him, while in John 10:39, they sought again to take him.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 39, 42, 4, 29, 30, 'escaped out of their hand', 'Escape from Hostility', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of Jesus escaping from hostile situations. In John 10:39, he ''escaped out of their hand,'' while in Luke 4:30, he ''passing through the midst of them went his way.''', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 39, 43, 10, 31, 31, 'sought again to take him', 'Attempts to Harm Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the Jews'' intent to harm Jesus, with John 10:31 showing their initial aggression by taking up stones, and John 10:39 illustrating their continued efforts to seize him. This connection highlights the escalating hostility towards Jesus.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 40, 43, 1, 28, 28, 'beyond Jordan', 'Location of John''s Baptism', 'Both passages emphasize the location beyond Jordan where John baptized. This connection highlights the significance of the place in relation to Jesus'' ministry.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 40, 43, 3, 26, 26, 'beyond Jordan', 'Connection of Baptism and Location', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of the location beyond Jordan, where John baptized. The reference to John in both contexts highlights the continuity of his ministry and the impact of Jesus'' actions in that same area.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 40, 43, 7, 1, 1, NULL, 'Jesus'' Movement and Safety', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' movements in response to threats. In John 7:1, Jesus avoids Judea due to danger, while in John 10:40, he retreats to a safer location beyond Jordan.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 40, 43, 11, 54, 54, 'went away again beyond Jordan', 'Jesus'' Movement and Location', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' movement to different locations. In John 10:40, he goes beyond Jordan, while in John 11:54, he moves to a country near the wilderness.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 41, 43, 1, 33, 34, 'all things that John spake of this man were true', 'Witness to Jesus'' Identity', 'Both passages emphasize the testimony of John regarding Jesus. In John 10:41, it is noted that John spoke truthfully about Jesus, while John 1:33-34 highlights John''s recognition of Jesus as the Son of God.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 41, 40, 3, 11, 12, 'all things that John spake of this man were true', 'Connection of John and Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize John the Baptist''s role in relation to Jesus. John acknowledges that he baptizes with water, while Jesus will baptize with the Holy Ghost, affirming John''s testimony that ''all things that John spake of this man were true.''', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 41, 40, 4, 23, 25, 'all things that John spake of this man were true', 'Connection of Jesus'' Healing Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the impact of Jesus'' ministry, highlighting how people were drawn to him due to his teachings and miraculous healings. The mention of John the Baptist in John 10:41 as a truth-teller about Jesus complements the portrayal of Jesus'' fame and healing works in Matthew 4:23-25.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 41, 41, 1, 37, 37, NULL, 'Seeking Jesus and Testimony', 'Both passages emphasize the interest in Jesus, with people actively seeking him. The mention of John the Baptist''s truthful testimony in the source verse highlights the growing recognition of Jesus''s significance, which is echoed in the target passage where all men seek for him.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 41, 42, 5, 1, 1, 'many resorted unto him', 'Crowds Seeking Jesus'' Teachings', 'This connection highlights the theme of people gathering to hear Jesus, as seen in both passages. In John 10:41, many resorted to Jesus, while in Luke 5:1, the people pressed upon him to hear the word of God.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 41, 42, 7, 26, 30, 'John did no miracle', 'John the Baptist''s Prophetic Role', 'Both passages emphasize John the Baptist''s significance as a prophet. John is acknowledged for speaking truthfully about Jesus, and Jesus affirms John''s role as a messenger preparing the way. This connection highlights the recognition of John''s prophetic authority.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 41, 43, 1, 27, 27, 'all things that John spake of this man were true', 'Connection of John the Baptist''s Testimony', 'Both passages emphasize John the Baptist''s role in relation to Jesus. In John 10:41, the truth of John''s testimony about Jesus is affirmed, while John 1:27 highlights John''s acknowledgment of Jesus'' superiority.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 42, 43, 4, 41, 41, 'believed on him there', 'Belief in Jesus'' Words', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of belief in Jesus. In John 10:42, many believed on him, while John 4:41 notes that many more believed because of his own word.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 42, 43, 2, 23, 23, 'many believed on him there', 'Belief in Jesus'' Miracles', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of belief in Jesus, specifically noting that many believed in him due to the miracles he performed. In John 2:23, belief is triggered by witnessing his miracles, while John 10:42 reflects the ongoing impact of his ministry in fostering belief.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 42, 43, 4, 39, 39, 'believed on him', 'Belief in Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of belief in Jesus. In John 10:42, many believed on him, while in John 4:39, many Samaritans believed based on a woman''s testimony about him.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 42, 43, 7, 31, 31, 'believed on him', 'Belief in Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of belief in Jesus, as many people recognized his miracles and came to faith in him. The phrase ''believed on him'' appears in both contexts, linking the responses of the people to his works.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 42, 43, 8, 30, 30, 'many believed on him', 'Belief in Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the response of belief in Jesus. In John 8:30, many believed on him as he spoke, and in John 10:42, many believed on him there, indicating a consistent theme of belief in his words.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 42, 43, 11, 45, 45, 'believed on him', 'Belief in Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of belief in Jesus, as indicated by the phrase ''believed on him.'' The first passage notes that many believed in him, while the second passage highlights that many Jews, after witnessing his miracles, also believed.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 42, 43, 12, 42, 42, 'many believed on him', 'Belief in Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize belief in Jesus, with many individuals acknowledging him. However, the second passage highlights the fear of social repercussions that prevented some from openly confessing their faith.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
